Class LocalEncryptedRecord

  • Object
    • com.tozny.e3db.LocalEncryptedRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EncryptedRecord, Signable, SignedDocument<EncryptedRecord>

    public class LocalEncryptedRecord
extends Object
implements EncryptedRecord
    An implementation of EncryptedRecord that can be converted to a string (using encode()) or loaded from a string (using decode(String).

    • Constructor Detail

      • LocalEncryptedRecord

        public LocalEncryptedRecord(Map<String,String> data,
                            ClientMeta meta,
                            String signature)
        Create an instance with encrypted data, metadata, and the given signature.

        This constructor should generally not be called directly; instead consider using Client.encryptRecord(String, RecordData, Map, EAKInfo) or Client.encryptExisting(LocalRecord, EAKInfo).

        Parameters:
        data - Encrypted data. Cannot be null.
        meta - Metadata associated with the record. Note that only server-specific metadata will be ignored (i.e, RecordMeta.created(), RecordMeta.lastModified(), etc.). Cannot be null.
        signature - Signature of the plaintext data and metadata. Cannot be null.
